   "body" : "As described in `util/ref.h`: \"_This implements a small subset of the functionality in C++17's std::any class, and **can be dropped when the project updates to C++17**_\". The interface for checking for and accessing the contained object is a bit different for `std::any`. The following pattern for getting an object of type `Type&` out of the container with `util::Ref` is commonly used in master branch:\r\n\r\n```\r\nutil::Ref ref = ...;\r\nif (ref.Has<Type>()) {\r\n    Type& x = ref.Get<Type>();\r\n} else {\r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is semantically equivalent to the `std::any` version:\r\n\r\n```\r\nstd::any any = ...;\r\ntry {\r\n    Type& x = std::any_cast<std::reference_wrapper<Type>>(any);\r\n} catch (const std::bad_any_cast&) {\r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```",
